{"slideshow_credits": null, "snippet": "When secret tests a decade ago showed its airbags could crack and explode, the company tried to erase the evidence, former employees said.", "abstract": "Two former employees of Japanese manufacturer Takata say when secret tests in 2004 showed that its airbags could crack and explode, company deleted test data and disposed of airbag inflaters instead of alerting federal safety regulators to possible danger; eleven automakers have recalled more than 14 million vehicles worldwide because of rupture risks, and four deaths have been tied to defect.", "section_name": "Business Day", "print_page": "1", "document_type": "article", "byline": {"person": [{"firstname": "Hiroko", "role": "reported", "lastname": "TABUCHI", "rank": 1, "organization": ""}], "original": "By HIROKO TABUCHI", "contributor": "Christopher Jensen contributed reporting."}, "web_url": "http://www.nytimes.com/2014/11/07/business/airbag-maker-takata-is-said-to-have-conducted-secret-tests.html", "lead_paragraph": "When secret tests a decade ago showed its airbags could crack and explode, the company tried to erase the evidence, former employees said.", "headline": {"main": "Takata Saw and Hid Risk in Airbags in 2004, Former Workers Say", "print_headline": "Airbag Maker Hid \u201904 Tests, 2 Workers Say"}, "_id": "545c13a538f0d85e5ee91999", "word_count": "1936", "multimedia": [{"height": 126, "url": "images/2014/11/07/business/07takata-web1/07takata-web1-thumbWide-v2.jpg", "legacy": {"wideheight": "126", "wide": "images/2014/11/07/business/07takata-web1/07takata-web1-thumbWide-v2.jpg", "widewidth": "190"}, "subtype": "wide", "width": 190, "type": "image"}, {"height": 370, "url": "images/2014/11/07/business/07takata-web1/07takata-articleLarge.jpg", "legacy": {"xlarge": "images/2014/11/07/business/07takata-web1/07takata-articleLarge.jpg", "xlargewidth": "600", "xlargeheight": "370"}, "subtype": "xlarge", "width": 600, "type": "image"}, {"height": 75, "url": "images/2014/